## CRITICAL REMINDERS

**On duplicates:** The single biggest CTR killer on Mirellé is multiple pages sharing one title. Every page gets a unique title matched to its specific content. No exceptions.

**On accuracy:** A clickbait title that oversells causes a bounce. Google tracks that round trip. Write titles that are compelling AND accurate — they must describe what's actually on the page.

**On identity:** For aesthetic clusters (quiet luxury, old money, dark feminine, soft girl, mob wife, office siren) — the user is searching for herself, not just designs. Mirror who she is or aspires to be. She must see herself in the title.

**On how-to pages:** Remove fear in the title. "No Salon", "At Home", "5 Steps", "No Drill" — these phrases eliminate the intimidation barrier that stops people from clicking.

**On color/skin tone pages:** Lead with the frustration. Most women have been let down by generic color guides that don't account for their skin tone. Call that out directly in the description.

**On Google rewriting your titles:** Google rewrites titles that are off-topic, keyword-stuffed, or too long. Follow the rules above and rewrites will be minimal. If Google does rewrite — it means the title drifted from page content. Fix the accuracy, not the length.

